cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.CY 

This paper analyzes the productivity and impact of scientific research, which suggests it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper uses bibliometric indicators to analyze the impact of scientific publications. Other likely categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.CY (Computers and Society), as these categories also deal with the analysis of data and information.
